Hdata = h5read('higgs_100000_pt_1000_1200.h5', '/higgs_100000_pt_1000_1200');
QCDdata = h5read('qcd_100000_pt_1000_1200.h5','/qcd_100000_pt_1000_1200');
histogram(Hdata(4,:))
%for 1 sigma value we take poisscdf at 126.6 and compare value to 2.87*10^-7 or 1 in 3.5 million chance
%higgsmcdf = find(poisspdf(Hdata(4,:),126.6) < 2.87*10^-7 ) ;
%onesigma = (81882) + (higgsmcdf(end) - 81882)/5;
%significance = 81882/onesigma %or 95.82%
%similarly for background QCD at mean 177.3
histogram(QCDdata(4,:)) %sigma at 31756
qcdmcdf = find(poisscdf(QCDdata(4,:),126.6) < 2.87*10^-7);
A = linspace(11.9845,791.955,100000);
qonesigma = (14696)+ (qcdmcdf(end) - 14696)/5 ;
valueforonesigma = A(round(qonesigma))
valueforonesigma = 259.6666
significanceqcd = 14696/qonesigma
significanceqcd = 0.4628
histogram(Hdata(4,:))
hmcdf = find(poisscdf(Hdata(4,:),126.6) < 2.87*10^-7);
Ah = linspace(22.7749,154.6137,100000);
honesigma = (78752)+ (hmcdf(end) - 78752)/5 ;
valuehforonesigma = Ah(round(honesigma))
valuehforonesigma = 132.1323
significanceqcdh = honesigma/74556
significanceqcdh = 1.1126
%finding out Number of higgs and number of QCD where ratio = Nhiggs / sqrt(Nqcd)
%Nhig = hmcdf > 78752;
%Nhiggs = max(size(find(hmcdf.*Nhig)));
%Nqcd = 100000- 78752 ;
%ratio = Nhiggs/sqrt(Nqcd)
%for mass cuts I'm going systematically from 1-sigma to 5-sigma
sigmaHdata = std(Hdata(4,:));
mHdata = mean(Hdata(4,:));
masscutdata = [Hdata(4,:);Hdata(4,:);Hdata(4,:);Hdata(4,:);Hdata(4,:)];
n = [1 2 3 4 5];
mcuts = sigmaHdata.*n.';
for i = 1:5
ns(i) = mHdata - mcuts(i) ;
ps(i) = mHdata + mcuts(i);
cutteddataps(i,:) = masscutdata(i,:) < ps(i);
cutteddatans(i,:) = ns(i) < masscutdata(i,:);
end
cutteddata(1:5,:) = cutteddataps.*cutteddatans ;
newdata1 = Hdata(4,find(cutteddata(1,:)));
newdata2 = Hdata(4,find(cutteddata(2,:)));
newdata3 = Hdata(4,find(cutteddata(3,:)));
newdata4 = Hdata(4,find(cutteddata(4,:)));
newdata5 = Hdata(4,find(cutteddata(5,:)));
% now for the background
for j = 1:5
cuttedbgps(j,:) = QCDdata(4,:) < ps(j) ;
cuttedbgns(j,:) = ns(j) < QCDdata(4,:);
end
cutbg(1:5,:) = cuttedbgps.*cuttedbgns;
newbg1 = QCDdata(4,find(cutbg(1,:)));
newbg2 = QCDdata(4,find(cutbg(2,:)));
newbg3 = QCDdata(4,find(cutbg(3,:)));
newbg4 = QCDdata(4,find(cutbg(4,:)));
newbg5 = QCDdata(4,find(cutbg(5,:)));
significance = (10^-5)*50*max(size(newdata1))/(sqrt(2000*(10^-5)*max(size(newbg1))))
significance = 3.1363
significance2 = (10^-5)*50*max(size(newdata2))/(sqrt(2000*(10^-5)*max(size(newbg2))))
significance2 = 2.3398
significance3 = (10^-5)*50*max(size(newdata3))/(sqrt(2000*(10^-5)*max(size(newbg3))))
significance3 = 1.9540
